00:00:04.260 --> 00:00:07.860
Hi guys!
Before we begin, what is bunny jumping?

00:00:08.040 --> 00:00:14.520
Bunny jump or bhop is a combination of keyboard
strokes and mouse movements used to move faster,

00:00:14.520 --> 00:00:18.369
avoid attacks and in some cases to make less
noise.

00:00:18.369 --> 00:00:24.039
The sad news is that it's not as effective
as it was in Source (CS:Source) and 1.6 (CS

00:00:24.039 --> 00:00:26.210
1.6).
And the last thing I wanna/want to bring up:

00:00:26.210 --> 00:00:32.340
It's a lot harder to bhop on 64 tick servers
when you compare with 128 tick because it's

00:00:32.340 --> 00:00:37.320
less consistent and the jumps are less accurate.
The first rule of bunny jumping is that you

00:00:37.320 --> 00:00:44.829
need to bind the jump to something spammable
for when you land e.g. the mouse wheel.

00:00:44.829 --> 00:00:49.280
Some people like to scroll up to jump and
some like to scroll down.

00:00:49.280 --> 00:00:55.960
This is a personal preference.
To bind scroll up, type this, and for scroll

00:00:55.960 --> 00:01:01.080
down, type this.
You can now jump with scroll.

00:01:01.220 --> 00:01:07.240
Try jumping forward with scroll and as soon
as you land make sure to scroll so you instantly

00:01:07.260 --> 00:01:11.920
jump when landing.
Right after your first jump, stop pressing

00:01:11.920 --> 00:01:17.210
forward and let yourself bhop.
This is the very basics of bhop.

00:01:17.210 --> 00:01:22.180
Now, type cl_showpos 1.
This will bring up some information in the

00:01:22.180 --> 00:01:27.920
corner and we're gonna focus on velocity.
The velocity is normally on 250 when running.

00:01:27.920 --> 00:01:33.060
To effectively bhop, your velocity has to
be between 250 and 300.

00:01:33.060 --> 00:01:38.520
You can go faster than 300, but your speed
will be decreased automatically.

00:01:38.520 --> 00:01:44.009
So how do we get between 250 and 300?
This is where you need to use the air acceleration

00:01:44.009 --> 00:01:47.049
to your advantage.
How do you do that?

00:01:47.049 --> 00:01:52.740
You do it through strafe movements in the
air.

00:01:52.740 --> 00:01:57.049
When moving left in the air with your mouse,
you need to press the A key.

00:01:57.049 --> 00:02:00.649
When moving right in the air, you need to
press the D key.

00:02:00.649 --> 00:02:07.520
Otherwise, it looks like this.
